  "title": "Workplace Safety & Health Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Roles and Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li>Work as a safety assessor role for the Permit-To-Work (PTW) system</li><li>Assist the WSHO in organizing safety awareness activities such as toolbox meetings, safety orientation, safety- related training, safety promotional activities, etc.</li><li>Identify any unsafe condition in the worksite or unsafe work practice in the worksite</li><li>Recommend and implement reasonably practicable measures to remedy the unsafe condition/work practice</li><li>Work with the site staff to eliminate and rectify any foreseeable risk and hazard in the work site.</li><li>Carry out daily inspection and reports any unsafe practices or conditions immediately to the management.</li><li>Monitor sub-contractor on their safety performance and compliance.</li><li>Assist to investigate all site incidents/accidents & implement corrective measures to prevent a recurrence.</li><li>Keeping record and documentation on the issuance of personal protection equipment(PPE), PTW, toolbox meeting, attendance, etc</li><li>Enforces all safety requirements and in-house safety rules and regulations.</li></ul><p></p><p><u><strong>Requirements</strong></u><br /></p><ul><li>Minimum 3 years working experience of WSHC. Experienced in pipe jacking  or tunneling work will be advantage.</li><li>Registered and qualified by Commissioner for Workplace Safety and Health </li><li>Competent to perform the function and duties of a WSHC</li></ul><p>Possess following certificate: </p><p>a)      Safety coordinators course from approved institutes<br />b)      Work at height assessor<br />c)      Confined space assessor<br />d)      Confined space rescuer <br />e)      Work at height assessor<br />f)       Lifting supervisor<br />g)      First Aider</p><ul><li>Positive attitude, team player and committed to continuous improvement</li></ul>",
